 :tx/rationale "Set t-0988fa40 title=EXT-BUG-5: braid init detects cargo in Go-only project. When running braid init in a Go project, the meta-extractor probes for build systems and incorrectly detects Cargo (because braid itself is a Cargo project). BACKGROUND: The meta-extractor in init.rs checks for Cargo.toml, go.mod, package.json etc. to auto-configure extractors. If braid's own Cargo.toml is accessible (e.g., via PATH or working directory traversal), it false-positives. Related to C8-FIX-1 (scope to project dir). FIX: (1) In meta-extractor detection (init.rs), only check for build files in the project directory (path argument), not in braid's own install directory. (2) Use the same project-dir scoping from C8-FIX-1: never walk above the .braid parent. (3) Specifically: check path.join(Cargo.toml).exists(), not which cargo or cargo metadata. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid init in Go project: detects go.mod, does NOT detect Cargo.toml. (B) braid init in Rust project: detects Cargo.toml correctly. (C) braid init in mixed project: detects both. (D) No false positives from braid's own build files. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs"
